# PicoClaw Setup Commands (Windows)

## Prerequisites
Install Go 1.21+, Node.js 18+, and Git before starting.
  Go:     https://go.dev/dl/
  Node:   https://nodejs.org/
  Git:    https://git-scm.com/

---

## 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/sipeed/picoclaw.git
cd picoclaw

## 2. Build the binary
go build -o build\picoclaw.exe .\cmd\picoclaw\
  (or double-click build-windows.bat)

## 3. Run first-time onboarding
.\build\picoclaw.exe onboard
  -> Creates config at %USERPROFILE%\.picoclaw\config.json
  -> Edit that file to add your API key

## 4. Start the gateway
.\build\picoclaw.exe gateway

## 5. Start the web interface (second terminal)
cd web-interface
npm install
npm start
  -> Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser

---

## Optional: Electron desktop app (auto-starts gateway)
cd web-interface
npm install
npm run electron

## Optional: Build a distributable Windows installer
cd web-interface
npm run dist:win
  -> Produces installer in web-interface\dist\

## Optional: Run tests
go test ./...
